name: dfs.replication
description:
Default block replication. 
  The actual number of replications can be specified when the file is created.
  The default is used if replication is not specified in create time.

name: dfs.block.scanner.volume.join.timeout.ms
description:
The amount of time in milliseconds that the BlockScanner times out waiting
    for the VolumeScanner thread to join during a shutdown call.

name: yarn.app.mapreduce.am.container.log.backups
description:
Number of backup files for the ApplicationMaster logs when using
    ContainerRollingLogAppender (CRLA). See
    org.apache.log4j.RollingFileAppender.maxBackupIndex. By default,
    ContainerLogAppender (CLA) is used, and container logs are not rolled. CRLA
    is enabled for the ApplicationMaster when both
    yarn.app.mapreduce.am.container.log.limit.kb and
    yarn.app.mapreduce.am.container.log.backups are greater than zero.

name: dfs.datanode.slow.io.warning.threshold.ms
description:
The threshold in milliseconds at which we will log a slow
    io warning in a datanode. By default, this parameter is set to 300
    milliseconds.

name: dfs.namenode.available-space-rack-fault-tolerant-block-placement-policy.balanced-space-tolerance
description:
Only used when the dfs.block.replicator.classname is set to
    org.apache.hadoop.hdfs.server.blockmanagement.AvailableSpaceRackFaultTolerantBlockPlacementPolicy.
    Special value between 0 and 20, inclusive. if the value is set beyond the scope,
    this value will be set as 5 by default, Increases tolerance of
    placing blocks on Datanodes with similar disk space used.

name: dfs.datanode.cache.revocation.polling.ms
description:
How often the DataNode should poll to see if the clients have
    stopped using a replica that the DataNode wants to uncache.

name: dfs.datanode.socket.reuse.keepalive
description:
The window of time in ms before the DataXceiver closes a socket for a
    single request.  If a second request occurs within that window, the
    socket can be reused.

name: mapreduce.input.lineinputformat.linespermap
description:
When using NLineInputFormat, the number of lines of input data
  to include in each split.

name: mapreduce.reduce.cpu.vcores
description:
The number of virtual cores to request from the scheduler for
  each reduce task.
